history.text: Hello, how are you?
Good, how are you?
I'm great thanks. So, what did you think of Batman Begins?
Definitely one of my favorite story lines for the Batman series, though I wasn't (and am not) a big Christian Bale fan.
What do you think?
I thought it was really good too. It had a much darker tone than most superhero movies. I totally forgot Liam Neeson was even in it.
And I think this is the last time I even saw Katie Holmes in something.
Haha, yeah.  I always knew he was a big name through the years but he never had a big spotlight.
Yeah you might be right about her.  Tom Cruise kind of ruined her career.
Yea, I like his movies. Well until he started doing Taken over and over again. But I like all his other movies.
haha he sure did, didn't he?
I'm kind of surprised this wasn't rated higher on rotten tomatoes.
Michael Caine is one of my favorite actors though.  Ever see Now You See Me?  He was great in that
Marvel movies get such high scores
Meh, I don't give them much credit anymore
Yea I did see that, that was great. I didn't realize that was the same guy though.
I liked that movie.
Was Bane in this movie?
Tom Hardy I think his name is?
No, Bane didn't come around until the film from 2016 -- I think
Oh ok, gotcha.
I know that one well because it was filmed in Pittsburgh, PA and I live close to there
Oh, that's pretty neat. I never get to see my city in anything.
Actually there was a sci fi tv show called fringe that was filmed here
but I never recognized anything
Yeah, I try to find movies that were filmed there because it's cool to see familiar scenes
Oh yea, Morgan Freeman was in this. I love that dude. He did great.
I think I saw every movie he was in from like 99-2009, haha
There's been so many batmans now
haha thats awesome. He's been in so many
Yet again -- fences was a Morgan freeman flick and it was filmed in Pittsburgh,lol
lol wow that must be a really beautiful city
Yeah -- I personally think all the superhero movies are getting out of hand, but they're entertaining
It's a good set for movies, because it's made up of 90 individual neighborhoods that all go by their own name.  So every few blocks is like a new town.
Oh absolutely. It's like movies are only made for children now.
Ah I see. That must be fun to get to see stuff you know on the screen like that with movie stars. But yea, from all these superhero movies, to robots and whatever else, It's taking a toll.
and now people are trying to find ways to politicize them and what not. It's ridiculous.
Yeah.  I was good with the first Transformers being all there was.  Then they kept making more...
hahah right?
and they swap out characters like the story doesn't even matter. Because it doesn't really.
But I feel like Batman Begins and the one after it had a decent story line. I felt like it was an actual movie. Not just eye candy.
Sadly that's true anymore
Movies are better when you read the books first, it's like you're on the inside, haha
Well, I think our 20 minutes are up.  Want to wrap this thing up and make the big bucks?
lol oh wow that was quick. Yea for sure. It's been a pleasure
Hope to talk to you again soon
Yeah, it was actually fun.  Have a good one!

uid1response.feedback: I was pleasantly surprised at how this HIT went.  The conversation was natural and two-sided.
